  "text": "This audit identified five core TLS/SSL implementation files in Firefox's Network Security Services (NSS) library located in security/nss/lib/ssl/ directory:\n\n1. **ssl3con.c** (github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8:security/nss/lib/ssl/ssl3con.c): Implements SSL 3.0/TLS record processing and cipher suite negotiation. Key functions include ssl3_SendRecord (line 2667) which sends TLS records, and ssl3_HandleRecord (line 13721) which processes incoming records. This file contains the cipher suite configuration table and handshake message processing logic.\n\n2. **tls13con.c** (github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8:security/nss/lib/ssl/tls13con.c): Implements TLS 1.3 handshake and record processing. Core functions include tls13_SendServerHelloSequence for server-side handshake initialization, tls13_HandleCertificate for certificate processing, tls13_SendFinished for finished message generation, and tls13_ComputeHandshakeSecrets/tls13_ComputeApplicationSecrets for key derivation following TLS 1.3 specification.\n\n3. **dtlscon.c** (github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8:security/nss/lib/ssl/dtlscon.c): Implements DTLS-specific protocol handling including version mapping between TLS and DTLS formats. Key functions are dtls_TLSVersionToDTLSVersion (line 59) and dtls_DTLSVersionToTLSVersion (line 81) which perform wire format conversions, plus dtls_RetransmitTimerExpiredCb (line 610) which handles retransmission timeout events - critical for UDP-based DTLS reliability.\n\n4. **ssl3ecc.c** (github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8:security/nss/lib/ssl/ssl3ecc.c): Implements ECC cipher suite operations including elliptic curve parameter handling. Key functions are ssl_NamedGroup2ECParams (line 35) for converting named curves to EC parameters, ssl_ECPubKey2NamedGroup (line 70) for extracting named curves from public keys, and ssl3_SendECDHServerKeyExchange (line 675) for ECDH key exchange in cipher suites.\n\n5. **sslexp.h** (github.com/sg-evals/firefox--871325b8:security/nss/lib/ssl/sslexp.h): Header file declaring experimental SSL APIs not guaranteed to persist in future NSS versions. Provides extension management capabilities including SSL_GetExtensionSupport and SSL_InstallExtensionHooks macros for custom TLS extension handling."
